# Terraform Standards — vsrp_sandbox_env

## 1. Comments

- Add explanatory comments to all Terraform code.
- Use block-level comments (`#` or `/* */`) to describe *what* each resource/module does and *why* (e.g., security, cost, architecture).
- Document non-obvious values, constraints, or dependencies.
- Keep comments concise; avoid stating the obvious.

## 2. Terraform Registry Modules

- Prefer Terraform Registry modules (especially `terraform-aws-modules/*`) over raw resources.
- Use modules to get full configurations upfront (encryption, lifecycle, monitoring, etc.) and avoid adding configs later.
- Pin module versions in the `source` (e.g., `terraform-aws-modules/ecr/aws` with `version = "~> 3.0"` in `required_providers` or `source`).
- When using a module, pass all relevant variables to configure it fully rather than accepting defaults blindly.

## 3. Module Choices (Reference)

| Resource        | Module                               |
|----------------|--------------------------------------|
| ECR            | terraform-aws-modules/ecr/aws        |
| ALB            | terraform-aws-modules/alb/aws        |
| ECS            | terraform-aws-modules/ecs/aws        |
| RDS            | terraform-aws-modules/rds/aws        |
| Security Group | terraform-aws-modules/security-group/aws |
